                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13510511" author="shamib007" created="Wed, 5 Dec 2012 14:45:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We can have a solution by extending the FilterFunc class in Pig. The exec() method implementation will be like :&lt;br/&gt;
    String firstStr = (String)input.get(0);&lt;br/&gt;
    String secondStr = (String)input.get(1);&lt;br/&gt;
    return new Boolean(firstStr.equalsIgnoreCase(secondStr));&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;where input is the argument to exec() method.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13526398" author="shamib007" created="Fri, 7 Dec 2012 14:05:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please find the attached UDF for Equals Ignore.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13560949" author="alangates" created="Wed, 23 Jan 2013 18:56:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;First, let me apologize for taking so long to get to this.  We should have reviewed it a lot sooner.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patch looks fine.  It needs tests however.  You need to add unit tests to check that this UDF correctly compares strings.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13565308" author="shamib007" created="Tue, 29 Jan 2013 12:16:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the review comments.&lt;br/&gt;
I am working on the unit test cases and will submit it soon.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13565344" author="shamib007" created="Tue, 29 Jan 2013 13:15:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please find the attached unit test case for the EqualsIgnore UDF.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13565346" author="shamib007" created="Tue, 29 Jan 2013 13:16:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please find the attached unit test case for EqualsIgnoreCase UDF&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13565550" author="alangates" created="Tue, 29 Jan 2013 17:33:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll review this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13569017" author="alangates" created="Fri, 1 Feb 2013 19:52:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching a single patch with the previous two combined.  I also took the liberty of expanding the unit test to have a negative case.  This patch represents what I will check in.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13569217" author="alangates" created="Fri, 1 Feb 2013 23:07:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch 1 checked into trunk.  Thanks Shami for your work on this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13971860" author="mrflip" created="Wed, 16 Apr 2014 20:50:57 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;It should fail when more than one input is passed to the UDF: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    ff = FILTER franchises BY EqualsIgnoreCase(franch_id, &apos;bOs&apos;, &apos;shouldfail&apos;); &amp;#8211; should fail, doesn&apos;t&lt;br/&gt;
    DUMP(ff);&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;#8211; (BOS,Boston Red Sox,Y,)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Should I re-post as a separate bug, or is a comment here appropriate?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
